CRM stands for Customer Relationship Management.

It is a system used by companies to manage customer information, communication, sales, and services in one place.

CRM helps companies:

Store customer details
Track interactions
Improve customer relationships
Increase sales
Provide better support

Why Companies Use Salesforce
Companies use Salesforce because it helps them
Manage customer data easily
Track sales and business deals
Improve communication with customers
Automate business processes
Provide better customer service
Access data from anywhere using cloud technology
Generate reports and analytics
An Account represents a company, organization, or customer business.
A Contact is a person associated with an account.
An Opportunity represents a potential sale or business deal.